    <!-- Terms of Service Screen -->
    <string name="tos_title">Terms of Service</string>
    <string name="tos_header">Terms of Service for the SeniorAssistant mobile application</string>
    <string name="tos_section1_title">1. General Provisions</string>
    <string name="tos_section1_content">• SeniorAssistant is a mobile application designed for the Android system, whose goal is to support communication between older people and volunteers.\n• The Terms and Conditions define the rules for providing services, terms of use of the application, and the rights and obligations of Users.\n• Downloading, registering, and using the application means acceptance of these Terms and Conditions.</string>
    <string name="tos_section2_title">2. Glossary of Terms</string>
    <string name="tos_section2_content">• Application – SeniorAssistant mobile software.\n• User – any person holding an account in the Application (Senior, Volunteer, or Administrator).\n• Senior – an older person using the Application to obtain support.\n• Volunteer – a person registered for the purpose of providing unpaid assistance.\n• Administrator – the person managing the system.</string>
    <string name="tos_section3_title">3. Registration and Account Types</string>
    <string name="tos_section3_content">• Use of the full functionality of the Application requires creating an account (Senior or Volunteer).\n• The User is obliged to provide true and current contact details.\n• Each User can edit their data at any time from the main panel.</string>
    <string name="tos_section4_title">4. Application Functionalities and User Roles</string>
    <string name="tos_section4_content">• Senior account enables: creating help requests, setting reminders for visits and medications, communication with the AI Assistant.\n• Volunteer account enables: browsing active reports and declaring willingness to implement them.\n• Administrative Panel serves to manage the system and moderate content.</string>
    <string name="tos_section5_title">5. AI Assistant and Integrations</string>
    <string name="tos_section5_content">• The application has a built-in integration with the AI Assistant.\n• Content generated by the AI Assistant is for informational and auxiliary purposes only. It does not replace specialist advice (e.g., medical or legal).</string>
    <string name="tos_section6_title">6. Important Health and Safety Disclaimers</string>
    <string name="tos_section6_content">• The application IS NOT a medical device. The reminder function is auxiliary. The creators are not responsible for omitting a dose of medicine.\n• The application IS NOT USED to call for help in life-threatening situations. You should then call 112.\n• Volunteers provide assistance voluntarily, as far as possible. The application does not guarantee finding a volunteer for every request.</string>
    <string name="tos_section7_title">7. User Rights and Obligations</string>
    <string name="tos_section7_content">• Users are obliged to use the Application in accordance with the law and respect for others.\n• It is forbidden to publish offensive content or use the Application for commercial purposes.\n• The Administrator may block an account that violates the Terms and Conditions.</string>
    <string name="tos_section8_title">8. Final Provisions</string>
    <string name="tos_section8_content">• The creators of the Application reserve the right to make changes to the Terms and Conditions.\n• In matters not regulated, the relevant provisions of Polish law shall apply.</string>

